# Cursor Rules for Amplify DataStore Todo App

This project uses modular cursor rules organized in the `.cursor/rules/` directory.

## Rule Files

- `.cursor/rules/version-control.mdc` - Version control, commits, and push workflow
- `.cursor/rules/typescript.mdc` - TypeScript best practices
- `.cursor/rules/react-native.mdc` - React Native component patterns
- `.cursor/rules/component-architecture.mdc` - Component architecture and separation of concerns
- `.cursor/rules/testing.mdc` - Unit testing requirements
- `.cursor/rules/aws-amplify.mdc` - AWS Amplify DataStore conventions
- `.cursor/rules/documentation.mdc` - Documentation standards
- `.cursor/rules/project-management.mdc` - Project todos and workflow
- `.cursor/rules/ui-ux.mdc` - UI/UX design patterns

All rules are automatically applied. See individual rule files in `.cursor/rules/` for detailed guidelines.
